        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 15 at 3:35AM CDT by NWS Aberdeen SD</headline>
        <description>At 334 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Brandt, or 8 miles south of Clear Lake, moving northeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Watertown, Clear Lake, Estelline, Castlewood, Goose Lake, Lake
Poinsett, Hayti, Summit, Rauville, Gary, South Shore, Toronto,
Waverly, Kranzburg, Goodwin, Astoria, Revillo, Stockholm, Brandt, and
Hazel.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

To report severe weather, contact your nearest law enforcement
agency. They will relay your report to the National Weather Service
office in Aberdeen.</instruction>
